WEBVTT

00:00:00.079 --> 00:00:02.874
Are we designed to nap during the day?

00:00:03.291 --> 00:00:05.418
[Sleeping With Science]

00:00:07.920 --> 00:00:12.091
Most people aim to get their
recommended seven to nine hours of sleep

00:00:12.091 --> 00:00:14.427
in one long stretch at night.

00:00:14.427 --> 00:00:17.638
And the technical term for this
is “monophasic sleep.”

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:21.017
In other words, a single bout
of sleep at night.

00:00:21.059 --> 00:00:22.226
However,

00:00:22.226 --> 00:00:26.022
we may not have been programmed
to sleep in this way.

00:00:26.064 --> 00:00:28.858
Now I'm sure you've had that experience

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:32.111
of a drop in your alertness
in the afternoon,